1
00:00:02.500 --> 00:00:09.988
Reliability is one of the most critical attributes defining the overall quality and value of a product or system.

2
00:00:09.988 --> 00:00:13.540
High reliability is not achieved by chance.

3
00:00:13.540 --> 00:00:28.540
It is the result of deliberate decisions made throughout the entire lifecycle, including robust design, appropriate material selection, controlled manufacturing processes, effective quality assurance, and well-structured maintenance strategies.

4
00:00:28.540 --> 00:00:37.564
Each of these activities contributes to higher costs in production, acquisition, and ownership, but they also protect against far greater losses.

